
How to install mysql and set it up on Ubuntu:

# install the thw sql srever
sudo apt install mysql-server

# setup the server software
sudo mysql_secure_installation

# create a user for nano
sudo mysql
> CREATE USER 'nano'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'password123';
> GRANT PRIVILEGE ON *.* TO 'nano'@'localhost';

# now you should be able to login with password123
mysql -u nano -p
